sentences: She was born on 14 August 1980 in Las Gabias, Granada in southern Spain.
She has performed with her father since age seven and recorded her first album in 2001, Mi Cante Y Un Poema (My Songs and A Poem).
She released her third album, Mujeres (Women) in 2006, which her father produced.
On 14 December 2001 she married bullfighter Javier Conde in Nuestra Señora de las Angustias basilica in Granada.
They have two children, Curro (2002) and Estrella (2005).
They have two children, Curro (2002) and Estrella (2005).
In the summer of 2004 she presented, in Granada, the concert "Estrella 1922" a tribute to the Sevillian singer Pastora Pavón, la Niña de los Peines, recorded live for its later edition.

In 2005 she made her debut at the Barbican Center in London and started a series of shared concerts with her father Enrique, commissioned by the International Festival of the Guitar of Córdoba.
In addition, the show "Estrella 1922" premiered also at the Teatro Español in Madrid that same year.

Morente was the voice behind Penélope Cruz's flamenco song in the 2006 film Volver.
She played herself in the 2011 animated feature Chico & Rita.

On 15 February 2014 the short film "Caen Piedras desde el Cielo" (Stones fall from the skies), by director Rafael Robles "Rafatal", premiered in Malaga, Spain, starring Estrella Morente as the protagonist, "Luz".
The short film is about a single mother in the 1970s working in a religious hospital and the obstacles she faced.
In 2001 she was named Ambassador of Andalusia by the Andalusian Institute of Youth.
In 2006 she was nominated for Latin Grammy and won the 2006 Music Award for Best Flamenco Album.
In 2006 she was nominated for Latin Grammy and won the 2006 Music Award for Best Flamenco Album.

In 2014 she was awarded the Medalla de Andalucía and was named director of the first Chair of Flamencology of the World taught by the San Antonio Catholic University of Murcia (UCAM) and the Cante de las Minas Foundation.
This was followed the same year by  Calle del Aire, which was well received by critics and flamenco fans.
Estrella's debut as a singer took place at the presentation gala of the Alpine Ski Championships in Sierra Nevada, being only 16 years old.

Her first album, "Mi cante y un poema" (My folk song and a poem) composed of flamenco songs was platinum and the second, "Calle del aire" (Air Street) composed of popular and Christmas songs, was gold.

At the beginning of 2008 received the Best Live Show Award, after an international survey conducted by the digital newspaper deflamenco.com, in addition to the "Flamenco Hoy" Award in its ninth edition, for the best flamenco DVD, "Casacueva y Escenario".
